#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat <<'EOF'
usermin-node — install and operate a Usermin web interface service

COMMANDS
  version            Print the package version
  daemon install     Add the official repo and install usermin
  daemon enable      Enable the boot service
  daemon start       Start the usermin service
  daemon stop        Stop the usermin service
  daemon restart     Restart the usermin service
  daemon status      Check whether usermin is running
  daemon monitor     Tail the miniserv log
  daemon disable     Stop and disable the service

USAGE
  usermin-node daemon install
  usermin-node daemon enable && usermin-node daemon start
  # then open https://127.0.0.1:20000

USERMIN PROVIDES
  - A per-user web interface (mail, password change, SSH keys)
  - Home-directory file manager, cron, GnuPG, and more
  - Webmin's sibling: ordinary users self-serve, root admin stays in
    Webmin (see webmin-node)

PER-USER, NOT ROOT ADMIN
  Usermin's miniserv authenticates any local account and runs each
  session as that user — end users get only their own files and mail,
  never host administration. Restrict access with the firewall and/or
  miniserv.conf 'allow=' rules; front it with a reverse proxy for a
  public hostname.

SERVICES
  Web UI:  https://127.0.0.1:20000

FILES
  Binary/libs:  /usr/share/usermin
  Config:       /etc/usermin/ (miniserv.conf, miniserv.users)
  Logs:         /var/log/usermin/miniserv.log

PLATFORM
  Linux only (apt/dnf). macOS is not packaged by this node.

SETUP
  1. Install:        usermin-node daemon install
  2. Enable + start: usermin-node daemon enable && usermin-node daemon start
  3. Log in:         https://<host>:20000 as any local user

SEE ALSO
  usermin-node-daemon(1), webmin-node(1)
  https://www.webmin.com/usermin.html
EOF
